A video of a crash between a Ferrari 488 GTB and a Corsa
Utility bakkie is doing the rounds on social media. On the CCTV footage, a white Toyota Etios can be seen making
a u-turn and the Utility bakkie follows suit – while trying to make the u-turn,
the red Ferrari comes speeding and crashes into the bakkie. The costs to fix the damages will not come cheap to the
person who caused the accident. A Ferrari 488 GTB costs over R5.5 million and while a 2017 Corsa
Utility bakkie costs about R130 000. The incident reportedly occurred Somerset Road in Green
Point. 